# ===================================================================
# .gitignore for charleschale/excstds-claude (the "brains" repo)
# ===================================================================
# Strategy: maximize what gets backed up. Push all methodology, all
# tooling, all prototype working notes, all reference data. Exclude
# only:
#   1. Things with their own backup (_pipeline lives in its own repo)
#   2. Polished client deliverables (kept local for confidentiality)
#   3. Raw respondent data pulls (regeneratable from the pipeline)
#   4. Secrets (.env, credentials)
#   5. Regeneratable bloat (node_modules, .venv, __pycache__)
#   6. The brains snapshot zip (regeneratable; circular if included)
# ===================================================================

# --- Has its own backup repo ---
_pipeline/

# --- Polished client deliverables (real-name reports, kept LOCAL) ---
_reports/

# --- Raw respondent data pulls (regeneratable from pipeline) ---
_respondents/

# --- Stray accidental directory ---
C:/

# --- Regeneratable artifacts ---
brains_snapshot_*.zip
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/

# --- OS / editor cruft ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~
~$*

# --- Secrets — never commit ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ===================================================================
